article.headline: Denver 67, Chicago St 60
article.story: CHICAGO (AP) -- Brett Starkey scored 25 points and Erik Benzel added 20 Saturday as Denver beat Chicago State 67-60 for its first win of the season. Starkey also had eight rebounds and Benzel shot 6-for-13 from the 3-point line. Denver took a 27-22 lead into halftime, but Chicago State hit their first five shots of the second half and took the lead with 16:16 left in the game. Denver regained the lead at 13:08 on consecutive lay-ups by Starkey, and did not fall behind again. Denver led by as many as nine points in the second half. Chicago State's Craig Franklin scored 27 points on 9-of-20 shooting. Rubeen Perry led Chicago state with 7 rebounds.
